Definition: a body of religious and philosophical beliefs and cultural practices native to India and based on a caste system
Example: it is characterized by a belief in reincarnation, by a belief in a supreme being of many forms and natures, by the view that opposing theories are aspects of one eternal truth, and by a desire for liberation from earthly evils
Synonyms: Hindooism, religion, a, body, of, religious, and, philosophical, beliefs, cultural, practices, native, to, India, based, on, caste, system, it, is, characterized, by, belief, in, reincarnation, supreme, being, many, forms, natures, the, view, that, opposing, theories, are, aspects, one, eternal, truth, desire, for, liberation, from, earthly, evils
Category: noun.cognition
